  <section>
    <h>dependents</h>
    <section id="sbj">
      <h>subject</h>
      <p>Older pedagogical examples – <xl id="sbj-older-pedag">
          <li>
            <gd><m>Tha mo mhàthair</m> a’ sgrìobhadh litreach gu <m>m’athair a tha</m> air falbh.
              Thubhairt mo mhàthair, “An téid thu do bhocsa nan litrichean leis an litir seo, Iain?”
              “Théid,” ars Iain, “falbhaidh mi an dràsda”. “Fuirich gus an dùin mi i is gus an cuir
              mi seòladh oirre. Ceannaich fhéin stamp agus cuir oirre i.” <m>Tha Iain</m> a’ ruith
              sìos an rathad leis an litir ’na làimh. Théid e a steach do oifig a’ phuist,
              ceannaichidh e stamp is cuiridh e sud air an litir. Tilgidh e an litir ann am bocsa
              nan litrichean. </gd>
            <tr>My mother is writing a letter to my father who is away. My mother said, “Will you go
              to the postbox with this letter, John?” “Yes, I will,” said John, “I will leave now.”
              “Wait until I seal it and put an address on it. Buy a stamp and put it on it.” John is
              running down the road with the letter in his hand. He will go into the post office, he
              will buy a stamp and put that on the letter. He will toss the letter into the
              postbox.</tr>
            <ref text="621">td. 5–6</ref>
          </li>
          <li>
            <gd><m>Bha an latha</m> brèagha blàth is thug an athair leis Iain agus Anna anns a’
              chàr. Chuir iad an càr a stigh gu taobh an rathaid is thug iad brat a mach as a’ chàr
              air son suidhe air. <m>Tha bascaid</m> làn de bhiadh aca is <m>tha iad</m> a’ dol a
              ghabhail an tea air a’ chnocan ghorm. Is toigh leis a’ chloinn biadh a ghabhail a
              muigh ri latha brèagha. Thèid iad dhachaidh feasgar an uair a <m>tha a’ ghrian</m> a’
              dol fodha.</gd>
            <tr>The day was lovely and warm and their father took John and Ann in the car. They put
              the car into the side of the road and they took a blanket out of the car for sitting
              on. They have a basket full of food and they are going to have their tea on the little
              green hill. The children like eating al fresco on a nice day. They will go home in the
              evening when the sun is going down.</tr>
            <ref text="621">td. 6</ref>
          </li>
        </xl>
      </p>
    </section>
