    <p><span lang="en">Notes</span><span lang="gd">Notaichean</span> – <ol id="notes">
        <li><span lang="en">The future forms <b>bidh</b> and <b>bhios</b> have the emphatic alternatives <b>bithidh</b> and <b>bhitheas</b>.</span>
          <span lang="gd">Tha cruthan eile airson na cruthan teachdail <b>bidh</b> agus <b>bhios</b> – <b>bithidh</b> agus <b>bhitheas</b>.</span>
        </li>
        <li><span lang="en">The conditional forms <b>b(h)iodh</b> and <b>b(h)iomaid</b> have the emphatic alternatives <b>b(h)itheadh</b> and
              <b>b(h)itheamaid</b>.</span>
          <span lang="gd">Tha cruthan eile airson na cruthan cumhach <b>b(h)iodh</b> agus <b>b(h)iomaid</b> – <b>b(h)itheadh</b> agus
            <b>b(h)itheamaid</b>.</span></li>
        <li><span lang="en">The passive forms in <b>-ar</b> have alternatives in <b>-as</b> – <b>thathas</b>, <b>eileas</b>, <b>bheileas</b>,
              <b>bhathas</b>, <b>robhas</b>, <b>b(h)itheas</b>.</span>
          <span lang="gd">cf. <b>-ar</b> an àite <b>-as</b> – <b>thathas</b>, <b>eileas</b>, <b>bheileas</b>, <b>bhathas</b>,
              <b>robhas</b>, <b>b(h)itheas</b>.</span></li>
        <li><span lang="en">Note also <b>thatar</b>, <b>bhatar</b> and <b>b(h)itear</b> as alternatives to <b>thathar</b>, <b>bhathar</b> and
              <b>b(h)ithear</b>.</span>
          <span lang="gd">cf. <b>thatar</b>, <b>bhatar</b>, <b>b(h)itear</b> an àite <b>thathar</b>, <b>bhathar</b>,
            <b>b(h)ithear</b>.</span></li>
        <li><span lang="en">The conditional passive form <b>b(h)istist(e)</b> is sometimes found as an alternative to <b>b(h)ite</b>.</span>
          <span lang="gd">cf. <b>b(h)istist(e)</b> an àite <b>b(h)ite</b>.</span></li>
        <li><b>chan eil</b> was often written <b>cha’n’eil</b> in traditional orthography. Similarly, <b>a bheil</b> was often written (and presumably pronounced)
            <b>am beil</b>.</li>
      </ol>
    </p>
